                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.113/101: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France (<persName type="from"
                            >Edge</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-28T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 28, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received July 28—8:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>450. Your 265, July 27, 6 p.m. In conversation with M. <persName corresp="#p_HE1"
                        >Herriot</persName> last evening, reported in another telegram,<note n="41"
                        xml:id="d149fn41">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> I informally brought up the subject of the Franco-Belgian agreement and
                    its discrimination against the United States, specifically mentioning the copper
                    matter. The Prime Minister has asked me for a memorandum outlining the
                    situation, which is now being prepared.</p>
                <pb facs="0329" n="239" xml:id="pg_239"/>
                <p>Replying to the last paragraph of the Department’s telegram under reference, it
                    is my understanding that France does not accord nations other than Belgium this
                    special 2 percent advantage covered by the Franco-Belgian treaty. I am further
                    informed that Switzerland has already put retaliatory measures in effect.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Edge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
